node_modules/
        .env
        .DS_Store
        ```
4.  **Add Remote:** Replace the URL with your actual repo link.
    ```bash
    git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
    ```

### 3. Build the "Election Assistant" Logic
In your `app.js` (if using Node.js), you’ll want to integrate the API key you generated in **Screenshot 2026-05-01 at 5.26.06 PM.jpg**.

*   **Install SDK:** Run `npm install @google/generative-ai express dotenv`.
*   **Code Template:**
    ```javascript
    const { GoogleGenerativeAI } = require("@google/generative-ai");
    require('dotenv').config();

    const genAI = new GoogleGenerativeAI(process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY);
    // Add logic to handle election questions here...
    ```

### 4. Prepare for Cloud Run (The `Dockerfile`)
Google Cloud Run needs to know how to "start" your app. Create a file named `Dockerfile` (no extension) and paste this:

```dockerfile
FROM node:18
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install
COPY . .
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["node", "app.js"]